trend_summary: Imagery shows a predominantly rural mosaic shifting between forest and cropland. Early frames have mixed woodland and small fields; mid-period clearing enlarges pale crop blocks, followed by partial forest regrowth, and ending with renewed cultivation. Built fabric remains minimal, limited to a linear road corridor and scattered farmsteads.
notable_changes: Progressive enlargement of central and eastern crop fields, replacing woodland.
Temporary reforestation phase in mid-series, especially northwest sector.
Consistent presence and slight upgrading of the east-west highway/rail corridor.
Minor infill of farmsteads along the transport line; no major urban nuclei.
Field boundaries consolidate over time, indicating mechanised agriculture adoption.
